Program: Outlook
Title: 23/12/2009
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p005nhrq
Last Broadcast Date: Christmas Eve 2009
Personal stories behind the news from all over the world. With Matthew Bannister. A "behind the scenes" look at the service of Nine Lessons and Carols from King's College Cambridge. Outlook today celebrates one of the great Christmas traditions - the service of Nine Lessons and Carols from Kings College Cambridge. Matthew Bannister goes behind the scenes to hear about the preparations for the service which is heard by millions of people all over the world. Matthew meets some of the people involved in this iconic service including Alex Stobbs, the nineteen year old with cystic fibrosis who's been a member of the internationally famous choir since he was nine years old. Show less